CKA Module 1 — Core Concepts Labs
Lab 1.1 — Create a Deployment
Create a Deployment named web-deploy:

image: nginx:latest

replicas: 3

label: app=web

Expose it as a ClusterIP service on port 80.

Lab 1.2 — Create a Pod from YAML
Write a YAML file named redis-pod.yaml:

Pod name: redis

image: redis:7

containerPort: 6379

Apply it and verify logs.

Lab 1.3 — Create a DaemonSet
Create a DaemonSet named log-agent:

image: busybox

command: ["sh", "-c", "while true; do echo log-agent; sleep 5; done"]

Verify it runs on all nodes.

Lab 1.4 — Create a Job
Create a Job named pi-job that runs:

Code
perl -Mbignum=bpi -wle "print bpi(2000)"
🧭 CKA Module 2 — Scheduling Labs
Lab 2.1 — Taints & Tolerations
Taint worker‑1:

Code
kubectl taint nodes k8s-worker-1 key=value:NoSchedule
Create a Pod that can run on that node using tolerations.

Lab 2.2 — Node Selectors
Create a Pod that runs only on worker‑2:

Add label to worker‑2:

Code
kubectl label node k8s-worker-2 disk=ssd
Pod must have:

Code
nodeSelector:
  disk: ssd
Lab 2.3 — Affinity
Create a Deployment that uses podAntiAffinity so replicas never land on the same node.

🌐 CKA Module 3 — Networking Labs
Lab 3.1 — Create a NetworkPolicy
Deny all ingress to Pods labeled app=db except from Pods labeled app=api.

Lab 3.2 — Debug DNS
Deploy a busybox Pod:

Code
kubectl run dns-test --image=busybox:1.36 -- sleep 3600
Inside the Pod:

Code
nslookup kubernetes.default
Fix DNS if it fails.

Lab 3.3 — NodePort Service
Expose nginx as a NodePort service on port 30080.

Test from your laptop:

Code
curl http://<worker-node-ip>:30080
📦 CKA Module 4 — Storage Labs
Lab 4.1 — Create a PersistentVolume
Create a PV:

name: local-pv

capacity: 2Gi

accessMode: ReadWriteOnce

hostPath: /data/pv1

Lab 4.2 — Create a PVC
Create a PVC:

name: local-pvc

request: 1Gi

Bind it to the PV.

Lab 4.3 — Pod with PVC
Create a Pod that mounts the PVC at /mnt/data.

Write a file inside the Pod and verify it persists.

🔥 CKA Module 5 — Troubleshooting Labs
These are the labs that make you dangerous.

Lab 5.1 — CrashLoopBackOff
A Pod is stuck in CrashLoopBackOff.

Fix it using:

Code
kubectl logs
kubectl describe
kubectl edit
Lab 5.2 — Node NotReady
Simulate:

Code
systemctl stop kubelet
Fix the node and return it to Ready.

Lab 5.3 — CNI Failure
Delete CNI config:

Code
rm -rf /etc/cni/net.d/*
Fix the node so Pods get IPs again.

Lab 5.4 — kube-proxy Failure
Delete kube-proxy Pod:

Code
kubectl delete pod -n kube-system -l k8s-app=kube-proxy
Fix the cluster if Services break.

Lab 5.5 — etcd Backup & Restore
Backup:

Code
ETCDCTL_API=3 etcdctl snapshot save /root/backup.db \
  --endpoints=https://127.0.0.1:2379 \
  --cacert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/ca.crt \
  --cert=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.crt \
  --key=/etc/kubernetes/pki/etcd/server.key
Restore the cluster from the snapshot.
